-----------Spring-----------

Spring is a lightweight and popular open-source java-based framework.
Spring is developed by Rod Johnson in 2003.
It is used to develop enterprise-level applications.

//Features of Spring framework

    Feature 1. Inversion of control(IoC)
        The IoC container manages the lifecycle and configuration of application objects(beans) making it easier to manage dependencies and object creation.
        Benefits: Loose Coupling, Testability, Reusability, Modular design

    Inversion of control ek design principle hai, jisme object creation aur lifecycle ka control programmer se Spring Container ke paas chala jata h. Spring bolta h ki mai object create kar dunga.
        Spring IoC Container
        objects create karta h.
        objects manage karta h.
        Lifecycle control karta h.

    Feature 2. Dependency Injection(DI)
        Dependency Injection is a way to inject the dependency rather than having to create or manage them explicitly. 
        It is achieved through spring IoC container which is responsible for creating and managing objects known as beans.
        
        Dependency Injection IoC ka implementation hai jisme Spring required dependencies automatically inject karta h 
        instead of creating them using new keyword, which reduces tight coupling and makes application loosely coupled and easiest to test. 

//Types of Dependency Injection in Spring

    1. Constructor Injection
        public class car{
            private Engine engine;

            @AutoWired

            public car(Engine engine){
                this.engine=engine;
            }
        }


    2. Setter Injection

        public class car{
            private Engine engine;

            @AutoWired
            public void setEngine(Engine engine){
                this.engine=engine;
            }
        }

    3. Field Injection
        
        public class car{
            @AutoWired

            private Engine engine;
        }

    
    //Summary
    Ioc(Inversion of Control) is responsible for creating and managing beans.

    DI(Dependency Injection) is responsible for Injecting and created beans into other beans where they are needed.


    Feature 3. Aspect-Oriented Programming(AOP)
        AOP helps separate cross-cutting concerns(like logging, transaction management,security) from business logic.It allows you to add additional behaviour to code without modifying the code itself.


    Feature 4. Spring MVC
        A framework for building web applications, Spring MVC follows the Model-View-Controller(MVC) design pattern.It simplifies the development of web application by providing an efficient way to handle HTTP requests and responses.

    Feature 5. Transaction management   
        Makes it easier to handle database transactions in our applications.By using Spring's transaction management abstarction, we can focus on our business logic without worrying about the complex details of transaction management. It simplifies the process, reduces boilerPlate code, and helps ensure that your transactions are handled consistently across your application.

    Feature 6.
        A powerful and customizable authentication and authorization framework, Spring security handles security concerns at all layers, from the web layer down to the method level.

    Feature 7. Spring Boot
        Spring Boot is a tool that simplifies the development of new Spring applications. It comes with embedded servers(like Tomcat), auto-configuration, and production ready features such as metrices and health checks.


